{
  "_comment": "The canonical row registry for the roadmap matrix (eng review D11b): the row taxonomy lives HERE, never as constants inside the generator \u2014 adding a component is a registry edit, not a code edit. Columns are DERIVED by roadmap/generate.py: this file declares where each row's artifacts live (or will live); it never carries a status symbol. Judgment cells are annotated at the source they describe with tb-cell markers (schema: docs/skill-authoring.md).",
  "_row_kinds": "Typed rows (eng review 5A): absent 'kind' = component (the matrix above); 'kind': 'rule' = one pay-now rule, rendered in the second 'Pay-now rules' table (rule / taught in / enforced by / status) so external enforcers render honestly. Rule-row keys (narrow v1): taught_in = repo path (optional #anchor) where the rule is taught, existence-checked; enforced_by = free text naming the enforcer (external tools like import-linter live here; listing check codes on rule rows lands with the fused anatomy checks). A malformed kind is a named file:line error.",
  "_column_semantics": {
    "skill": "component-doc filename under skills/tesser-build/; absent key = n/a (\u2014); named-but-missing file = \u274c; present file's tb-status marker decides \u2705 (full) vs \ud83d\udfe1 (partial/stub)",
    "py_example, go_example": "candidate paths relative to repo root; absent key = n/a (\u2014); any path exists = \u2705; none exist = \u274c",
    "go_analyzers, py_checks": "names in internal/analyzers.All / codes in tessercheck.finding.CHECKS; a listed name missing from the live registry is a loud error (drift). Rendering: \u2705 requires BOTH lists non-empty; only one populated caps the cell at \ud83d\udfe1 ('Py only'/'Go only'); neither populated falls back to enforcement_tests (\ud83d\udfe1 in-example) and then \u274c. Absent key = n/a (\u2014), present-but-empty [] = \u274c planned-but-absent \u2014 the two are deliberately different",
    "enforcement_tests": "in-example enforcement test paths; these alone cap the checker cell at \ud83d\udfe1 in-example",
    "rationale": "glob patterns for executable-rationale test files; absent key = n/a (\u2014); no match = \u274c"
  },
  "_unrowed_semantics": "The totality guard (2026-07-21) inverts each enumerable universe — skill docs under skills/tesser-build/*.md, tessercheck-py CHECKS codes, internal/analyzers.All names — and fails when a member is claimed by no row. Every other check runs registry → repo ('what a row names exists'); this one runs repo → registry ('what exists is claimed'), the direction that let serialization.md, logging.md, TB015 and TB016 ship with no row at all. A member that genuinely belongs to no row goes here BY NAME WITH A REASON. An exemption that is also claimed by a row, or that names something no longer present, is a loud error — the exemption list must not become the new stale thing.",
